  "texts": [
    "At its start in November 2022, ChatGPT ran on GPT version 3.5 (GPT3.5).",
    "Previous versions of GPT from 1 to 3 exist and have been fine-tuned one after another, learning from predecessors' shortcomings to improve their results.",
    "At this date, the current version of GPT is 4o.",
    "GPT3 surpassed several existing pre-trained significant language model performances [39] with more than 500 GB of pre-trained data and 100 billion parameters, achieving accurate language analyses, interpretations, understanding, and descriptions.It is worth mentioning that the GPT3 model fine-tuning process was through reinforcement learning with human feedback (RLHF) which achieved huge success in finalizing the creation of ChatGPT [40].",
    "ChatGPT is attractive for its human-like query responses [41], its openness to the public, and its easiness of usage (through a chatbot)."
